"title": "1680: types",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1680",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An OT institution, person, place or event regarded as anticipating the person of Jesus Christ or some aspect of the Christian faith or life.</p>\n<h2>OT foreshadowings of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:25-Luke24:27\">LUK 24:25–24:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:44\">LUK 24:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:10-1Pet1:12\">1PE 1:10–1:12</a></p>\n<h2>OT institutions as types</h2>\n<h3>The Sabbath:  Jesus Christ's finished work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:3-Heb4:6\">HEB 4:3–4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:2-Gen2:3\">GEN 2:2–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:9-Heb4:10\">HEB 4:9–4:10</a></p>\n<h3>Marriage:  Jesus Christ's union with his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:30-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:30–5:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:22-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:22–2:24</a> <em>Adam may be viewed as a figure of Jesus Christ, and Eve, of the church, formed in Christ, loved and united with him</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:10-Ps45:11\">PSA 45:10–45:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:15\">MAT 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1\">MAT 25:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:29\">JHN 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></p>\n<h3>Circumcision: believers' union with Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11\">COL 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:9–17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:29\">ROM 2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>The tabernacle: Jesus Christ's coming among his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>The context shows that “The Word” is Jesus Christ; “made his dwelling” involves the idea of pitching a tent and reflects the tabernacle which was pitched among the Israelites and filled with God's glory; so Christ has pitched his tent among his people and revealed his glory.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8\">EXO 25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:34-Exod40:35\">EXO 40:34–40:35</a></p>\n<h3>The tabernacle: the way to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:12\">HEB 9:11–9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:22\">EXO 25:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:6\">EXO 30:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:36\">EXO 30:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:4\">NUM 17:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:8\">HEB 9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:22\">HEB 10:19–10:22</a></p>\n<h3>The high priesthood: Jesus Christ as intercessor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:23-Heb7:28\">HEB 7:23–7:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1-Exod29:7\">EXO 29:1–29:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:11-Lev16:17\">LEV 16:11–16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:14–4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:1-Heb5:5\">HEB 5:1–5:5</a> <em>Jesus Christ, the great high priest, is both human and divine</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:12\">HEB 9:11–9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:12\">HEB 10:11–10:12</a> <em>Note the contrast between the many OT sacrifices and Jesus Christ's once-for-all offering of himself.</em></p>\n<h3>The priesthood: Christian worship and service</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:15-Heb13:16\">HEB 13:15–13:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:6\">EXO 19:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:8-Exod29:9\">EXO 29:8–29:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:6\">REV 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifices: Jesus Christ as substitute</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:15\">LEV 4:13–4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:25-Lev4:35\">LEV 4:25–4:35</a> <em>Hands laid on the head of the sacrifice symbolised the transfer of guilt and its consequences to another. A perfect animal was required</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:4-Isa53:12\">ISA 53:4–53:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:25-Mark15:37\">MRK 15:25–15:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:15\">2CO 5:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifice: believers' consecration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:1-Lev1:9\">LEV 1:1–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:1-Num15:12\">NUM 15:1–15:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:17\">PHP 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:6\">2TI 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>The day of atonement: Jesus Christ as sin-bearer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:1-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:1–16:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>Passover: deliverance from judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:1-Exod12:16\">EXO 12:1–12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:17\">MAT 26:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:12\">MRK 14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:7\">LUK 22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:29\">MAT 26:26–26:29</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:25\">MRK 14:22–14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:14-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:14–22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:29\">JHN 1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a></p>\n<h3>Redemption: release from sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>“Redemption” and “ransom” both involve buying back that which has been lost.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:11-Exod13:13\">EXO 13:11–13:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:28-Exod21:32\">EXO 21:28–21:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25\">JOB 19:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:35\">PSA 78:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:14\">ISA 41:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:24\">ROM 3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:20</a>GAL <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:13\">3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5\">GAL 4:5</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a> <em>Blood is the ransom price for the forgiveness of sin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></p>\n<h3>The temple: the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:1\">1KI 6:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:10-1Kgs8:13\">1KI 8:10–8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:21-Eph2:22\">EPH 2:21–2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>OT places as types</h2>\n<h3>The promised land: rest in Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:8-Heb4:11\">HEB 4:8–4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:13\">JOS 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:23\">JOS 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:15\">JOS 14:15</a></p>\n<h3>Jerusalem: the glorified church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1-Rev21:3\">REV 21:1–21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:4-2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:4–5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps122:1-Ps122:9\">PSA 122:1–122:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:6-Isa62:7\">ISA 62:6–62:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech2:3-Zech2:5\">ZEC 2:3–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22-Heb12:23\">HEB 12:22–12:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:12\">REV 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9-Rev21:10\">REV 21:9–21:10</a></p>\n<h3>Babylon: enmity to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:5\">REV 17:5</a></strong> <em>Some take Babylon to represent the world, some the apostate church, some a city.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:19-Isa13:22\">ISA 13:19–13:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:2-Rev18:3\">REV 18:2–18:3</a></p>\n<h2>OT people as types</h2>\n<h3>Israel: the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:1–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:6\">EXO 19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:6-Rom9:8\">ROM 9:6–9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:16\">GAL 6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:19\">EPH 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Adam: Jesus Christ as the head of his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:21–15:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:17-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:17–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12-Rom5:20\">ROM 5:12–5:20</a> <em>Just as Adam was the representative of all humanity in the fall, so Jesus Christ is the representative of all who inherit salvation.</em></p>\n<h3>Abraham: justifying faith in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:18-Rom4:25\">ROM 4:18–4:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:9\">GAL 3:6–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Melchizedek: Jesus Christ as priest-king</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:1-Heb7:3\">HEB 7:1–7:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:17-Gen14:20\">GEN 14:17–14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:4\">PSA 110:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:11-Heb7:17\">HEB 7:11–7:17</a></p>\n<h3>Sarah and Hagar: grace and law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:22-Gal4:26\">GAL 4:22–4:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:1-Gen16:6\">GEN 16:1–16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:10\">GEN 21:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:27-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:27–4:31</a></p>\n<h3>David: Jesus Christ as king, shepherd and sufferer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:31-Luke1:33\">LUK 1:31–1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:11-2Sam7:16\">2SA 7:11–7:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:72\">PSA 78:70–78:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:19-Ps89:37\">PSA 89:19–89:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:18\">JHN 13:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>\n<h3>Solomon: Jesus Christ as wise ruler</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:42\">MAT 12:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:5-1Kgs3:12\">1KI 3:5–3:12</a></p>\n<h2>OT events as types</h2>\n<h3>Noah's ark: salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:20-1Pet3:21\">1PE 3:20–3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:7\">GEN 7:7</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham offering Isaac: God giving his Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:32\">ROM 8:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:9-Gen22:14\">GEN 22:9–22:14</a></p>\n<h3>Crossing the Red Sea: Christian commitment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:1-1Cor10:2\">1CO 10:1–10:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:15-Exod14:22\">EXO 14:15–14:22</a></p>\n<h3>Water from a rock: Jesus Christ's provision</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:4\">1CO 10:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:5-Exod17:6\">EXO 17:5–17:6</a></p>\n<h3>The bronze snake: Jesus Christ, the object of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:14-John3:15\">JHN 3:14–3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:4-Num21:9\">NUM 21:4–21:9</a></p>",
